# Linter and Analyzer Compliance

**ZERO TOLERANCE for linter errors and analyzer warnings.**

**Before every commit:**
```bash
flutter analyze                # Must return 0 issues
dart format --output=none --set-exit-if-changed .
```

**Common fixes:**
```dart
// ❌ Missing return type
getUser() async { }

// ✅ Declare return type
Future<User> getUser() async { }

// ❌ No const
Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(16))

// ✅ Add const
const Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(16))

// ❌ Avoid print
print('Debug message');

// ✅ Use logger
logger.d('Debug message');

// ❌ Missing key
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(context) { }
}

// ✅ Add key parameter
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyWidget({super.key});
  
  @override
  Widget build(context) { }
}

// ❌ Missing @override
class MyClass extends BaseClass {
  void method() { } // Overrides base
}

// ✅ Add @override
class MyClass extends BaseClass {
  @override
  void method() { }
}
```

**Auto-fix:**
```bash
dart fix --dry-run   # Preview fixes
dart fix --apply     # Apply fixes
dart format .        # Format code
```

**Suppressing (use sparingly):**
```dart
// Suppress with reason
// ignore: avoid_print
// Required for Flutter driver integration tests
print('Driver: Waiting for widget');
```

**ALWAYS:**
- Run analyze before committing
- Fix all warnings/errors
- Format code
- Enable linter in IDE
- Don't suppress without valid reason
